;THE N-TERMINAL 36 AMINO ACIDS OF THE PROTEIN WERE NOT
VISIBLE IN THE ELECTRON DENSITY.  PROTEIN SEQUENCE
ANALYSIS OF A REDISSOLVED CRYSTAL CONFIRMED THE PRESENCE
OF THE N-TERMINUS IN THE CRYSTALS.  THE CONCLUSION IS THEN
THAT THE N-TERMINAL 36 AMINO ACIDS ARE DISORDERED.
